class Solution {
    public int smallestRepunitDivByK(int k) {
        int remainder = 0;
        for (int length = 1; length <= k; length++) {
            remainder = (remainder * 10 + 1) % k;
            if (remainder == 0) {
                return length;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(K)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates up to k times, maintaining a running remainder when dividing the current number (comprised of 'length' number of 1s) by k. It returns the length as soon as it finds a number divisible by k. If no such number is found within k iterations, it returns -1, leveraging the property that if a remainder repeats, the sequence will loop and no new divisible numbers will be found.
